Former top Fifa official Chuck Blazer admits that he and others on the executive committee agreed to accept bribes in conjunction with the choice of South Africa as the 2010 foot ball World Cup host.The American says he also helped to arrange bribes over the 1998 event.The admissions come in a newly released transcript from a 2013 US hearing in which he pleads guilty to 10 charges.The US has launched a wide-ranging criminal case that engulfed Fifa and led President Sepp Blatter to resign.